.TH "DATATRANSFER.FILES" "3JS" "October 2, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
DataTransfer.files \- DataTransfer: files property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]files\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of
\f[CR]DataTransfer\f[R] objects is a list of the files in the drag
operation.
If the operation includes no files, the list is empty.
.PP
This feature can be used to drag files from a user\(cqs desktop to the
browser.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The \f[CR]files\f[R] property of \f[CR]DataTransfer\f[R]
objects can only be accessed from within the \f[CR]drop\f[R] and
\f[CR]paste\f[R] events.
For all other events, the \f[CR]files\f[R] property will be empty \(em
because its underlying data store will be in a protected mode.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]FileList\f[R] of the files in a drag operation, one list item
for each file in the operation.
If the drag operation had no files, the list is empty.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Reading the files list
This example creates a basic area that you can drop files into and
displays some metadata.
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]pre\f[R] id=\(dqoutput\(dq>Drop files here from your file system.</\f[B]pre\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
output {
  \f[B]min\-height\f[R]: 200px;
  \f[B]border\f[R]: 1px solid black;
  \f[B]padding\f[R]: 1em;
}
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] output = document.getElementById(\(dqoutput\(dq);

\f[B]function\f[R] log(text) {
  output.innerText += text;
}

output.addEventListener(\(dqdragenter\(dq, (e) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  e.stopPropagation();
  e.preventDefault();
  output.textContent = \(dq\(dq;
});
output.addEventListener(\(dqdragover\(dq, (e) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  e.stopPropagation();
  e.preventDefault();
});
output.addEventListener(\(dqdrop\(dq, (e) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  e.stopPropagation();
  e.preventDefault();
  \f[B]const\f[R] files = event.dataTransfer.files;
  log(\(gaFile Count: ${files.length}\(rsn\(ga);

  \f[B]for\f[R] (\f[B]const\f[R] file \f[B]of\f[R] files) {
    log(\(ga  File: ${file}, ${file.name}, ${file.size} bytes\(rsn\(ga);
  }
});
.EE
